body:
**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**
bug
**What is the current behavior?**
I'm trying to write a component that uses hooks. This component executes a request as an effect on component initial render with `useEffect`, and passing `[]` as its second param so the request only happens once. For some reason, in my test code, I can't this async call to resolve synchronously. I've made an [example repo](https://github.com/kyleholzinger/hooks-effect-bug-repro), but here are some code snippets so you don't have to navigate there! Here's the simple component I'm trying to render:

<details>
  <summary>Component</summary>

```jsx
function TodoList() {
  const [todos, setTodos] = useState([])

  useEffect(() => {
    console.log('executing effect')
    axios
      .get('https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos')
      .then((res) => {
        console.log('unwrapping request')
        return res.data
      })
      .then(setTodos)
  }, [])

  return (
    <div>
      some things:
      {todos.map((todo) => (
        <div className="todo" key={todo.id}>
          {todo.title}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  )
}
```

</details>

<details>
  <summary>Test code</summary>

```jsx
describe('<TodoList />', () => {
  let wrapper

  beforeEach(() => {
    console.log('mounting component')
    jest.useFakeTimers()
    axiosMockInstance = new MockAdapter(axios)
    axiosMockInstance
      .onGet('https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos')
      .reply(200, [{ id: 1, title: 'a thing' }])
    act(() => {
      wrapper = mount(<TodoList />)
      jest.runAllTimers()
    })
  })

  afterEach(() => {
    axiosMockInstance.restore()
  })

  it('calls its effect', () => {
    console.log('in example:')
    console.log(wrapper.debug())
    const todos = wrapper.find('.todo').at(0)
    console.log('this is a test')
    expect(todos.text()).toBe(10)
  })
})
```

</details>

<details>
  <summary>Screenshot of output when executing test</summary>

  ![failing test](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kyleholzinger/hooks-effect-bug-repro/master/images/before.png)

</details>

**What is the expected behavior?**
From my understanding of how everything is set up, I think that the combination of using `act` with `jest#runAllTimers` should be executing that effect as well as resolving the promise from axios within that `act` call, but it seems like the promise handlers are either not getting executed in time (I can't tell because jest intercepts logs), or if the component simply isn't rerendering after `setTodos` is executed. Sorry if this is a bit of a convoluted example, I couldn't find one much simpler! Also let me know if this should belong in jest or enzyme or something as well; I'm really unsure of where the bug lies. Thanks in advance for checking this out, I hope I can get this working! I've been really enjoying hooks so far üôè 

**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**
react: v16.8.6
enzyme: 3.9.0
